programme.title: E8: 178" Giant On Halloween, Best Buck Action Of The Season
programme.desc: Back for one of the most action filled episodes of the entire season, episode 8 perfectly embodies what draws so many deer hunters to prioritizing the pre-rut timeframe. Zach Rozmus draws his bow on the big buck he calls Squash with the deer at 10 yards. Gavin Koterba experiences the perfect pre-rut hunt and makes a great shot on a big eight point in Iowa. Mike Reed enjoys great buck action over the decoy using a creative setup. Owen Reigler continues his quest to fill the second buck tag of the season. Devin Wills hunts Halloween and punches his tag on a 178" giant in Iowa showcasing why morning hunts are starting to get good. Overall this window showcases of the best buck action of the season in season 10 of Chasing November.

programme.title: E15: 175" Rutcation Giant, Epic All Day Sit In A Rut Funnel
programme.desc: With November in full swing, rutcations all across the country are being cashed in to hunt the best time of year. Continuing down the tracks of November 8th where three bucks have already been tagged as seen in episode 14, this was only the beginning. Brooks Kehoe pulls an all day sit in a rut funnel and has a chaotic rut hunt seeing his target 3 different times before finally getting a shot on the Iowa hammer. Mike Reed continues his quest for the new double beam buck that recently showed up on camera a single time. Sean Thompson tags a 175" rutcation giant only 30 minutes into his sit. All in all, November 8th may go down as one of the best days of hunting for the Midwest Whitetail team ever.

programme.title: E19: A Public Land Giant Falls, New Bucks Are Showing
programme.desc: Continuing to navigate the final week of November, the team tackles the remaining hunts with poise. Mike Reed continues his grind to tag a buck electing to focus on the River Farm. Justin Karns comes to full draw on an Iowa bruiser in a unique treestand setup. Josh Dreyer continues his quest to fill his non-resident Iowa bow tag. Finally given the opportunity he's hunted so hard for, by the end of his hunt a public land giant falls. Josh Sparks shifts to public land to hunt a solid food source. With new bucks showing up and great hunting remaining, the team hunts on with excitement to round out the month.

programme.title: E10: Big Flyer Buck Down, November Rut Action Continues
programme.desc: Continuing into the first few days of November, the rut action continues full force. Zach Rozmus has a great standoff with a non-typical buck that showcases every aspect of what makes the rut so special. Justin Kamps has a great encounter with a big 8 point buck in Illinois. Mitch Mollerus has a heart break encounter in Missouri with a big 10. Bella Reed makes her first of the archery season. Elizabeth Marine closes a 4 year chapter on a big flyer buck leading to her best deer ever!

programme.title: E14: 173" Illinois Dandy, Three Bucks Down In One Morning
programme.desc: On this episode of Chasing November, we continue down the rut funnel for more epic hunting. The time to hunt the best stands is now and that's exactly what Zach Rozmus, Andy Melton, and Tyler Behlmann choose to do. From the crack of first light the bucks are on the move and all three have hunts that remind every deer hunter why November will always be king.
